FBIS3-16131 "drsov049_a_94043" FBIS-SOV-94-049 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Stepashin Discusses Case LD1103150694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1455 GMT 11 Mar 94 LD1103150694 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] [Text] Moscow March 11 TASS -- The recent arrest of a Russian citizen on charges of spying for Germany was a key issue of a telephone conversation between Sergey Stepashin, head of the Russian Federal Counter-Intelligence service (FCS), and German State Minister Bernd Schmidbauer on Friday [11 March], a spokesman for the Russian Counter-Intelligence Service told ITAR-TASS. Aleksandr Mikhailov, the FCS spokesman, said that "the conversation was of a professional character". The arrest was earlier officially confirmed by the agency. According to Mikhailov, "the arrest has no political bearing". The detainment of the German agent was the result of counter-intelligence activities aimed at securing Russia's state interests", he said.
